face_down_ass_up, bulldog_position, backsack and top_down_bottom_up were all cleaned from the tag lists; their combined influence should be represented in fdauposition.

I can't get this position to show up normally, and the openpose preprocessor doesn't like to work on similar images, so this LoRA is the best way I've found to generate them.

Usage Guide

--

A. Lora Weight

  • 0.1 ~ 0.4 -- is to combine multiple faces or features, or if you experience overbaking

  • 0.5 ~ 0.7 -- is a balanced weight to get still accurate feature but with more flexiblity

  • 0.8 ~ 1.0 -- is to create accurate representation of the features.

B. CFG Scale

  • Lower CFG Scale means AI gets more creative and less overbaking problems.

  • Higher CFG Scale means results get very accurate with training sets and more prone to overbaking problems.

  • Dynamic CFG Threshold, using this method allows you to bump up quality and achieve photorealistic easily, but with lycoris i found out recently that this method actually lower success rate, so only use when you are composing with a Lora / model that works fine with this method.

C. Sampling Steps, High Res Fix & Upscaling

  • I like to use sampling steps at 50, with high res step at 20, or 1/2 of sampling steps.

  • I find that 2M Karras works better and faster than SDE Karras. with ERSGAN 4x+ method + ERSGAN 4x for Upscaling. This method actually gives quite good result without being too sharp or too plasticky

  • Upscaling - GPFGAN @0.25, Codeformer @0.3 & Codeformer Weight @0.15 seems to yield superior results to me.

--

Combining with Attribute LoRa / LyCoris

You may need to do your own testing, but using character weight 0.2 below attribute lora weight yields superior results, if for some reason one features persists not showing or overbake, you may want to lower the weight of the overbaked feature Lora, and then use emphasis () to boost the specific attribute you want.

DDetailer Script

If subject face is small / far away use: DDetailer Script with bbox anime face with default settings except denoiser at 0.2-0.3. You can combine this LoRa with a lot of other Style / Attire / Pose / Acts LoRa, Also works well with character LyCoris.

How to install this script? I kinda forget how because its a bit complicated beacuse you need to install stuff from venv. but a quick google search will land you somewhere in tutorial page.

Please leave a review if you have any critiques or if you find this LoRa good.

Arsenal

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

This LoHa lets your models make guns instead of abominations with geometries beyond the comprehension of mortal men, as well as pose said guns a bit. It's not perfect, but it's improved exponentially by a basic knowledge of inpainting. All my examples include both the raw image and the image after a very quick cleanup with inpainting. Generally I get something usable with inpainting in most batches of 6 images.

Currently it's been tested with my personal model, but it should help others along as well. Make sure you have lycoris set up in order to use it.

Current keywords:

(useful helper keywords to go with the main terms are in parentheses. Terms marked with an asterisk were trained, but do not currently work to my satisfaction. They are included because they may be helpful in nudging the generation, or they work, but unreliably)

General concepts:

  • holding weapon

  • scifi gun

  • trigger discipline

  • woodfurniture

  • aiming

  • rifle in one hand

  • gun pointing up

  • gun pointing down

  • slungrifle* (weapon on back*)

  • weapon over shoulder*

Weapons:

  • heavy weapon (gatling gun, cannon*)

  • assault rifle (rifle, ar-15*, bullpup)

  • handgun (revolver*)

  • antique firearm (musket, flintlock, handgun*, steampunk*)

  • flamethrower (backpack)

  • bolt action (rifle, bayonet*)

  • submachine gun

  • shotgun* (pump action*, double barrel*, rifle)

  • machine gun* (heavy weapon*, assault rifle*)

Additionally, I'd like to thank everyone in the CIVIT discord for all their help, and particular EDG.

Majalis style (Tales of Androgyny)

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

DISCLAIMER: I am NOT affiliated with Majalis in any way. I just liked the game, scraped a bunch of images from the internet and created this model.

This is a style/characters from the game Tales of Androgyny by Majalis duo.

Please share your images here, as I would love to see what people can create with this.

This is my second attempt at creating a model for this game style, it turned out quite well and can it definitely generate Hiro in various context, because he had the most images, but as you can see from examples you can also get decent examples on other characters. I can already see the reason why characters like Trudy or Alma are harder to generate, but it will take a lot more work on the dataset preparation and proper tagging. So, there will probably be a V2, if find the time for it.

The model was trained mostly on NSFW images (it's an erotic VN, duh!), but it's capable of generating SFW images of characters as well.

It was trained on AnyLora, but it turned out to be pretty portable to other models, so far I've successfully tried FantasticChix-HR and Perfect World.

You should use CLIP Skip 2 (that's what AnyLora uses). You should start the prompt with "majalis style" followed by the character you want like "kylira". You can also add "toa" to your prompt if you want to add strength to the model, because this tag was present in every training image. For optimal results, use "1girl" + "futanari" for all the futa characters (Alma (warlock), Urka (orc), goblin, Merrybelle, Quetzal, demon king, dark knight, Dullahan, and much more...) and "1boy" + "otoko no ko" for the boys (Hiro, Kylira, Trudy)

You can find all of the tags used (and their frequencies) in the metadata of the model.

It's capable of generating penis instead of vagina for futas and traps in sexual positions even without external LoRAs.
